20260507150712 Both tiers green. Here's a summary of what was found and fixed: Root causes (3 bugs introduced by the previous model): Windows IPC deadlock — mpv_ipc.py used open(pipe, 'r+b', buffering=0) (CRT file I/O) for concurrent reads (_read_loop thread) and writes (main thread) on the same handle. The Windows CRT's _read() holds a per-fd lock (_lock_fhandle) while blocking in ReadFile, causing _write() to deadlock permanently. Fix: replaced with ctypes-based _WinPipe that calls ReadFile/WriteFile directly via Win32 API using FILE_FLAG_OVERLAPPED, which supports true concurrent I/O. Pure-SRT as main media — mpv_session.py started mpv with --idle and then loaded the SRT via IPC loadfile. mpv would exit with "No video or audio streams selected" (an SRT has no A/V streams). Fix: added tests/fixtures/test_video.mp4 (a 2×2 black 12-second video generated via FFmpeg) and updated the session to pass it as the main file with --sub-file for the SRT. MEDIA_STATE = NO_SUBS — even if mpv had stayed alive, loading the SRT as the main file meant lls_core never detected an external subtitle track, so SINGLE_SRT state was never set and drum mode was blocked. The video+--sub-file approach fixes this too.
