20260507155702 All three changes are in place and correct. Here's the summary: Root Cause The Sticky Sentinel (FSM.ACTIVE_IDX) that holds the active subtitle during the padding window existed only for the primary track. During continuous playback, whenever audio_padding_end + audio_padding_start exceeds the gap between two subtitles (e.g. sub 18 "Ja." → sub 19 with a ~0.9s gap and reasonable padding settings), the padded windows overlap: Primary: Sentinel holds sub 18 until its padded end expires Secondary: No sentinel → binary search Overlap Priority fires as soon as sub 19's padded start is reached → advances to sub 19 one tick earlier This is why rewind (a/d/click) fixes it: after a seek both tracks recalculate from the same exact timestamp and agree.
