20260509171121 The fix is in place. Here's a summary of what was happening and what changed: Root cause: FSM.DW_TOOLTIP_SEC_SUBS (the tooltip fallback cache) is only populated when a secondary subtitle track is actively selected (Tracks.sec.id ≠ 0). On restart with secondary subs disabled, neither the path-change block (line 3106–3110) nor the load block (3118–3123) runs, so the cache stays empty and the tooltip silently returns "". Fix (lls_core.lua:3118): After the existing load block, added a probe that runs when Tracks.sec.id == 0 and the tooltip cache is still empty. It scans the track list for the first external subtitle that isn't the primary track and loads it into FSM.DW_TOOLTIP_SEC_SUBS — exactly what happens when the user manually toggles secondary subs on and off during a session. This mirrors the post-toggle behavior that already works correctly, so the tooltip is available in Drum Mode from the moment the app starts, regardless of whether secondary subs are enabled.
