20260512104859 x Root cause traced and fixed. You’re hitting an overlap edge case introduced by the large padding model (`audio_padding_start=1000`, `audio_padding_end=1000`): pressing `d` seeks to the next subtitle’s padded start, but that timestamp can still be inside the previous subtitle’s raw SRT window. On the next `d`, index resolution snaps back to the previous line, so it feels “stuck” (while `a` still works). I patched manual seek anchoring to use the FSM sentinel index first (instead of transient `time-pos` overlap), which prevents this replay loop. Changed file: - [scripts/kardenwort/main.lua](/u:/voothi/20260308110646-kardenwort-mpv/scripts/kardenwort/main.lua:6331) What changed: - In `cmd_dw_seek_delta`, base navigation index now prefers `FSM.ACTIVE_IDX` (and still respects `FSM.DW_SEEK_TARGET` during hold-repeat). - Added a guard so we don’t early-return when `current_idx == -1` if sentinel is valid. Validation: - `luac -p scripts/kardenwort/main.lua` passed. Trace anchors relevant to this regression pattern: - `20260427161414` (previous stuck-scroll class) - `20260505103700` / `202605051144` period (multiple “d gets stuck” reports) - your current report `20260512103734` matches the same family but under current overlap/padding logic.
20260512105713 I retried from your rolled-back state and applied a deeper fix. What I changed in [main.lua](/u:/voothi/20260308110646-kardenwort-mpv/scripts/kardenwort/main.lua): 1. Sticky focus now uses tolerance around padded boundaries in `get_center_index`: - changed strict check `time_pos >= s and time_pos = (s - Options.nav_tolerance) and time_pos <= (e + Options.nav_tolerance)` 2. Re-applied sentinel-first navigation anchor in `cmd_dw_seek_delta`: - if `FSM.ACTIVE_IDX` is valid, use it as `base_idx` before fallback to transient `current_idx` - keep `DW_SEEK_TARGET` override during hold-repeat Why this should fix your exact case: - At `audio_padding_start=1000`, `d` seeks to padded start of next subtitle. - If mpv lands a few ms before that boundary, strict sticky logic can classify it as previous raw subtitle again, causing repeated “same line” forward jumps. - Tolerant sticky + sentinel anchor prevents that bounce-back. Validation performed: - `luac -p scripts/kardenwort/main.lua` passed. I could not run pytest here because this available interpreter lacks `pytest` (`No module named pytest`), so runtime confirmation needs your local test environment. If you want, I can also add a regression acceptance test that explicitly simulates this “seek lands slightly before padded start” condition so it stays locked in.
