20260512221335 How can I output in seconds? mpv.conf#L364-367
20260512221839 To output the replay duration in seconds, you can now use the %s placeholder in your templates. I've updated the implementation to support: %m: Milliseconds (e.g., 2000) %s: Seconds (e.g., 2) %c: Iteration count %x: Conditional count display Example configuration for mpv.conf: To show only seconds, you can change your format strings like this: ini # Displaying in seconds instead of milliseconds script-opts-append=kardenwort-replay_msg_format=Replay: %s sec%x script-opts-append=kardenwort-replay_on_msg_format=Replaying segment: %s sec%x I have already updated the documentation in your mpv.conf to include this new placeholder.
