20260513142156 Implemented: DM mini-window now has its own scrolloff option, and the `0` edge case is fixed. Changes made: 1. Added new option `drum_scrolloff` (default `0`) in [main.lua](u:/voothi/20260308110646-kardenwort-mpv/scripts/kardenwort/main.lua:238). 2. Updated visibility logic in [main.lua](u:/voothi/20260308110646-kardenwort-mpv/scripts/kardenwort/main.lua:6009) to: - Use DM mini viewport size when `DRUM=ON` and `DRUM_WINDOW=OFF`. - Use `drum_scrolloff` for DM mini mode, `dw_scrolloff` for DW mode. - Clamp margin safely with `max(0,...)`, so margin can never become `-1`. 3. Exposed config in [mpv.conf](u:/voothi/20260308110646-kardenwort-mpv/mpv.conf:171): - `script-opts-append=kardenwort-drum_scrolloff=0` 4. Documented the new parameter in [README.md](u:/voothi/20260308110646-kardenwort-mpv/README.md:501). About the `kardenwort-dw_scrolloff=0` problem: - The bug came from margin math that could go negative for tiny windows (`floor(win_lines/2)-1`), which can produce `-1`. - That negative margin lets the yellow pointer/viewport logic drift incorrectly. - Now margin is always clamped to `>= 0`, so `0` behaves correctly and predictably.
20260513142759 Error
20260513142817 Fixed the crash source in [main.lua](u:/voothi/20260308110646-kardenwort-mpv/scripts/kardenwort/main.lua). What was broken: - `ensure_sub_layout()` saved a reduced `layout_cache.entry` (no `height`, no draw metadata). - `dw_build_layout()` later reused that same cache and did `total_height + entry.height`, causing `attempt to perform arithmetic on field 'height' (a nil value)`. What I changed: 1. Added a compatibility guard in `dw_build_layout()` to reject partial cache entries and rebuild full draw layout: - [main.lua](u:/voothi/20260308110646-kardenwort-mpv/scripts/kardenwort/main.lua:3800) 2. Made `ensure_sub_layout()` include computed `height` in its cached entry to avoid nil arithmetic even in fallback paths: - [main.lua](u:/voothi/20260308110646-kardenwort-mpv/scripts/kardenwort/main.lua:5934) This should stop the repeating `master_tick crash` immediately after reload. If you want, I can now add a small regression test around this cache-shape mismatch so it can’t come back.
20260513143059 Error
20260513143110 Fixed this new crash in [main.lua](u:/voothi/20260308110646-kardenwort-mpv/scripts/kardenwort/main.lua:3800). Root cause: - We correctly detected invalid cached `entry` and set it to `nil`. - But rebuild logic was in `else`, so it never ran for the “cache exists but invalid” case. - Then code hit `table.insert(layout, entry)` with `entry=nil` and crashed (`attempt to index local 'entry'`). Patch: - Refactored flow to: 1. Try cache if valid. 2. `if not entry then` rebuild full entry. - This is now at [main.lua](u:/voothi/20260308110646-kardenwort-mpv/scripts/kardenwort/main.lua:3816). You can reload mpv/script now; this should stop the `line 3870`/`dw_build_layout` crash loop.
