20260514140745 Production Hardening Complete: Padding-Aware Navigation Resolution The activation issues encountered during pauses and segment transitions have been resolved. The core fix involves upgrading the snapshot engine to be "padding-aware," allowing it to see into the future of the upcoming subtitle's audio window. Enhancements Padding-Aware Binary Search: The resolution engine now incorporates AUDIO_PADDING_START into its deterministic search. This prevents the "snap-back" effect where navigation would target the previous subtitle during the initial ~1s padding of a new one. Lookahead Priority: If the playback timestamp is within the overlap of two subtitles (trailing padding of one and leading padding of the next), the engine now correctly prioritizes the upcoming subtitle for activation. Internal State Integrity: Removed the destructive FSM.DW_ACTIVE_LINE overwrite. The navigation resolution is now a pure context provider for the current event, ensuring that the script's internal player state remains synchronized with the official mpv events. Mathematical Parity: Simplified dw_compute_word_center_x to utilize the same layout cache as the rendering engine, guaranteeing that the yellow pointer always lands on the exact visual center of the targeted word. Validation Syntax: luac -p confirmed OK. Acceptance: pytest tests\acceptance\test_20260514001942_dm_dw_state_edges.py passed (6/6). The Drum Window navigation is now robust against engine latency and padding overlaps.
