20260514165416 I have resolved the issue where the Drum Window would remain stuck in manual mode after adding a selection to Anki (mining). Analysis of the Issue The dw_reset_selection() function was clearing the visual selection (Yellow/Pink) but failing to restore the logical state required for auto-maintenance. Specifically: FSM.DW_FOLLOW_PLAYER remained false, leaving the viewport frozen. FSM.DW_SEEKING_MANUALLY was not cleared. The active line was not synchronized to the live playback position, which could cause "stale" jumps if the player had moved during the selection process. Implementation Details I have unified the "Full Reset" logic into dw_reset_selection(), ensuring consistent behavior across both the Esc key (Stage 3) and the Anki export pipeline: Unified dw_reset_selection(): Added Live Line Synchronization: Now captures the authoritative playback index at the moment of reset to prevent viewport drift. Added Follow State Restoration: Automatically sets DW_FOLLOW_PLAYER = true and clears manual seeking flags. FSM Hardening: Simplified cmd_dw_esc to rely on the unified reset logic, reducing redundancy and potential state leakage. Instrumentation: Added dw_seeking_manually to the state snapshot for improved diagnostic visibility. Spec Alignment: Updated openspec/specs/pointer-auto-reset-triggers/spec.md to formally document the follow-state restoration requirement. Verification Results I created a new acceptance test test_20260514165416_reset_follow.py which verifies: PASS: Pressing Esc (Stage 3) restores auto-follow. PASS: Adding a word to Anki restores auto-follow. PASS: Manual seeking flags are correctly cleared upon reset. The existing test_20260501160807_dw_esc_staged_reset.py suite also passed, confirming that the staged "peel-back" logic for Esc remains intact. render_diffs(file:///u:/voothi/20260308110646-kardenwort-mpv/scripts/kardenwort/main.lua)
