20260514220322 Checked and fixed. You were hitting a real gap: in `auto_follow` mode, pressing `Esc` with no active selection had no transition branch, so follow was not restored to current subtitle. I changed design to one parameter with 3 values and fixed behavior: - New single option: - `kardenwort-dw_esc_mode=auto_follow_current|neutral_last_selection|neutral_current_subtitle` - Current config set in [mpv.conf](u:\voothi\20260308110646-kardenwort-mpv\mpv.conf:239): - `script-opts-append=kardenwort-dw_esc_mode=auto_follow_current` What each mode does: 1. `auto_follow_current` - `Esc` restores follow to current/live subtitle immediately (also when no selection exists). 2. `neutral_last_selection` - `Esc` goes to neutral first; next activation starts from last selected line. 3. `neutral_current_subtitle` - `Esc` goes to neutral first; next activation starts from current subtitle line. I also kept legacy parsing in code as fallback compatibility, but your active config is now single-parameter.
