20260514231607 I have finalized the release documentation for Kardenwort v1.80.30. The update consolidates the architectural improvements made to the navigation engine and state-machine synchronization implemented since v1.80.28. Summary of Changes for v1.80.30 Esc Reset Matrix & Neutral Mode: Implemented dw_esc_mode with three deterministic behaviors: auto_follow_current, neutral_last_selection, and neutral_current_subtitle. Introduced a Neutral Mode Sentinel (DW_ESC_NEUTRAL_ARMED) that allows users to analyze context in a frozen viewport before resuming follow-mode. Unified dw_reset_selection() to serve as the authoritative state-reset engine for both the Esc key and the Anki export pipeline. Mining Follow-Restoration: Resolved a critical state desync where the Drum Window would remain in manual mode after mining. The system now automatically restores DW_FOLLOW_PLAYER and re-synchronizes with the live playback line upon successful Anki export. Navigation Hardening: Enhanced priority resolution for null-selection activation: Neutral Marker -> Standing Cursor -> Active Line. Hardened the FSM against race conditions and state leakage during high-speed playback. Test Infrastructure Milestone: The project now maintains 741 passed acceptance tests. Integrated an automated Test Fixture Recovery bridge in conftest.py that restores TSV fixtures after test runs, ensuring a clean repository state. Documentation Updates release-notes.md: Added comprehensive highlights for v1.80.30, detailing the Esc matrix and neutral-mode logic. README.md: Updated version badges, maturity analytics, and added the new distinctive advantages (items 49-52). The release documentation is now fully synchronized with the repository state (commit 2a3b0001).
