20260515105704 I have implemented a Config-Driven Help system that allows you to manage all help descriptions and whitelists directly within your input.conf, while keeping safe defaults in the script. How to use it: You can now add special "meta-comments" to your input.conf to override the Help HUD data. This allows you to keep the descriptions right next to your keybindings. Format: # @help: | | Examples to add to your input.conf: properties # Overriding the Volume description and keys: # @help: volume | Master Volume | 9, 0 # Overriding the Smart Space description: # @help: kardenwort/smart-space | Play/Pause (Hold to Listen) | SPACE # Overriding Fullscreen: # @help: cycle fullscreen | Toggle Theater Mode | v, м Technical Details: Single Source of Truth: You can now centralize your changes in input.conf. If the script finds an @help tag for a command, it will prioritize your custom text over the hardcoded default. Automatic Fallback: If input.conf is missing or doesn't contain these tags, the HUD continues to function perfectly using the internal HELP_SCHEMA defaults. Dynamic Discovery: The HUD still dynamically searches for the keys; the WHITELIST part simply helps it filter out the "noise" (like mouse buttons) for that specific action. The system is now fully flexible and ready for your custom configuration!
